 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Loan Approval Prediction\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Classification Project 5 of 100** — Predict whether a loan application should be approved.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"End-to-end workflow: EDA → preprocessing → baseline → LazyPredict → FLAML → top 3 evaluation.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 2. Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Loan approval is a cornerstone of retail banking. Automating loan decisions helps banks process applications faster while maintaining credit quality.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"In this notebook we build a **binary classifier** that predicts whether a loan application should be approved using applicant demographics, income, credit history, and loan details from the classic Loan Prediction dataset.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Workflow:**\\n\", \"1. Download & validate the dataset from Kaggle\\n\", \"2. Perform thorough EDA with visualisations\\n\", \"3. Preprocess with sklearn pipelines (split-before-fit, no leakage)\\n\", \"4. Establish baselines (Dummy, LogReg, Random Forest)\\n\", \"5. Benchmark ~30 classifiers with LazyPredict\\n\", \"6. Run FLAML AutoML\\n\", \"7. Select & evaluate the top 3 models with full metrics\\n\", \"8. Analyse errors and extract business insights\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 3. Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"By completing this notebook you will learn to:\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Handle **mixed data types** (numeric + categorical) with `ColumnTransformer`\\n\", \"2. Impute **missing values** with appropriate strategies per column type\\n\", \"3. Apply **log transforms** to skewed income and loan amount features\\n\", \"4. Build a **leakage-free** preprocessing pipeline\\n\", \"5. Handle **moderate class imbalance** with stratification and class weights\\n\", \"6. Benchmark with **LazyPredict** and tune with **FLAML**\\n\", \"7. Compare multiple classification metrics for a lending context\\n\", \"8. Understand **fairness concerns** in automated loan decisioning\\n\", \"9. Extract **actionable business insights** about credit history, income, and property area\\n\", \"10. Reason about **false positive vs false negative costs** in loan approval\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 4. Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Given an applicant's demographics, income, credit history, and requested loan details, predict whether the loan should be approved.**\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This is a **binary classification** task. The target is `Loan_Status` (Y = approved, N = rejected). Missing a good applicant (false negative) loses revenue; approving a bad one (false positive) creates credit risk.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 5. Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Stakeholder | Impact |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Banks** | Faster, more consistent loan decisions |\\n\", \"| **Applicants** | Reduced wait times and more transparent criteria |\\n\", \"| **Risk teams** | Data-driven default risk assessment |\\n\", \"| **Regulators** | Auditable, explainable decision processes |\\n\", \"| **ML learners** | Practice handling missing data, mixed types, and fairness in financial ML |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 6. Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Name** | Loan Prediction Dataset |\\n\", \"| **Source** | Analytics Vidhya / Kaggle |\\n\", \"| **Kaggle slug** | `altruistdelhite04/loan-prediction-problem-dataset` |\\n\", \"| **Rows** | ~614 (train) |\\n\", \"| **Features** | 11 (demographics, income, loan details, credit history) |\\n\", \"| **Target** | `Loan_Status` (Y/N) |\\n\", \"| **Class balance** | ~69% approved, ~31% rejected |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Key columns:**\\n\", \"- `Gender`, `Married`, `Dependents`, `Education`, `Self_Employed` — demographics\\n\", \"- `ApplicantIncome`, `CoapplicantIncome` — income features\\n\", \"- `LoanAmount`, `Loan_Amount_Term` — loan details\\n\", \"- `Credit_History` — binary (1 = good history, 0 = bad)\\n\", \"- `Property_Area` — Urban / Semiurban / Rural\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 7. Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- **Source:** Analytics Vidhya Loan Prediction Practice Problem\\n\", \"- **Kaggle:** https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/altruistdelhite04/loan-prediction-problem-dataset\\n\", \"- **License:** Public dataset for educational use.\\n\", \"- **Note:** This is a small practice dataset (~614 rows). Results should be interpreted as learning exercises, not production benchmarks.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 8. Environment Setup\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"\\n\", \"for pkg in [\\\"lazypredict\\\", \\\"flaml\\\", \\\"kagglehub\\\"]:\\n\", \"    try:\\n\", \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\", \"    except ImportError:\\n\", \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 9. Imports\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import os, warnings, json, glob\\n\", \"import numpy as np\\n\", \"import pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\", \"import seaborn as sns\\n\", \"\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OneHotEncoder\\n\", \"from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\\n\", \"from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\n\", \"from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (\\n\", \"    accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\\n\", \"    roc_auc_score, average_precision_score,\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay, RocCurveDisplay, PrecisionRecallDisplay,\\n\", \"    classification_report\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyClassifier\\n\", \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\", \"\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\", \"sns.set_theme(style=\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"print(\\\"All imports loaded.\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 10. Configuration / Constants\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"KAGGLE_SLUG = \\\"altruistdelhite04/loan-prediction-problem-dataset\\\"\\n\", \"TARGET = \\\"Loan_Status\\\"\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.20\\n\", \"VAL_SIZE = 0.15\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"FLAML_BUDGET = 60  # seconds (small dataset)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Target: {TARGET} | Test: {TEST_SIZE} | Seed: {SEED}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 11. Dataset Download or Loading\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We use `kagglehub` to download the dataset. Kaggle credentials must be available.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import kagglehub\\n\", \"\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    path = kagglehub.dataset_download(KAGGLE_SLUG)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Dataset downloaded to: {path}\\\")\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    raise RuntimeError(\\n\", \"        f\\\"Failed to download dataset: {e}\\\\n\\\"\\n\", \"        \\\"Ensure KAGGLE_API_TOKEN is set or ~/.kaggle/kaggle.json exists.\\\"\\n\", \"    )\\n\", \"\\n\", \"csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path, \\\"**\\\", \\\"*.csv\\\"), recursive=True)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"CSV files found: {csv_files}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Use the train file\\n\", \"train_file = [f for f in csv_files if \\\"train\\\" in f.lower()]\\n\", \"if train_file:\\n\", \"    df_raw = pd.read_csv(train_file[0])\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    df_raw = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"df_raw.head()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 12. Data Validation Checks\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We verify data integrity: shape, columns, missing values, duplicates, and target distribution.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\nDtypes:\\\\n{df_raw.dtypes}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\nMissing values:\\\\n{df_raw.isnull().sum()[df_raw.isnull().sum() > 0]}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Drop Loan_ID\\n\", \"if \\\"Loan_ID\\\" in df_raw.columns:\\n\", \"    df = df_raw.drop(columns=[\\\"Loan_ID\\\"]).copy()\\n\", \"    print(\\\"\\\\nDropped Loan_ID.\\\")\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    df = df_raw.copy()\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Encode target\\n\", \"df[TARGET] = df[TARGET].map({\\\"Y\\\": 1, \\\"N\\\": 0})\\n\", \"assert df[TARGET].isnull().sum() == 0, \\\"Target has unmapped values!\\\"\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dupes = df.duplicated().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nDuplicate rows: {dupes}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTarget distribution:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Approval rate: {df[TARGET].mean():.1%}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 13. Exploratory Data Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We explore feature distributions, missing patterns, and relationships with the target.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"df.describe().T\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(15, 10))\\ncat_cols = [\\\"Gender\\\", \\\"Married\\\", \\\"Education\\\", \\\"Self_Employed\\\", \\\"Credit_History\\\", \\\"Property_Area\\\"]\\nfor ax, col in zip(axes.flat, cat_cols):\\n    if col in df.columns:\\n        df.groupby(col)[TARGET].mean().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n        ax.set_title(f\\\"Approval rate by {col}\\\")\\n        ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Approval Rate\\\")\\n        ax.set_ylim(0, 1)\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 4))\\nfor ax, col in zip(axes, [\\\"ApplicantIncome\\\", \\\"CoapplicantIncome\\\", \\\"LoanAmount\\\"]):\\n    if col in df.columns:\\n        df[col].hist(bins=30, ax=ax, color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n        ax.set_title(col)\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 14. Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"The target has ~69% approved, ~31% rejected — moderate imbalance. We use stratified splits and monitor both F1 and accuracy.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"approval_rate = df[TARGET].mean()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Approval rate: {approval_rate:.1%}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Rejection rate: {1 - approval_rate:.1%}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nClass counts:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Imbalance ratio: {approval_rate / (1 - approval_rate):.1f}:1\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 15. Train / Validation / Test Split Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We use a stratified 65/15/20 split. With only ~614 rows, careful stratification is critical.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET])\\n\", \"y = df[TARGET]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"X_temp, X_test, y_temp, y_test = train_test_split(\\n\", \"    X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y\\n\", \")\\n\", \"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(\\n\", \"    X_temp, y_temp, test_size=VAL_SIZE / (1 - TEST_SIZE),\\n\", \"    random_state=SEED, stratify=y_temp\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Train: {X_train.shape}  Val: {X_val.shape}  Test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"for name, ys in [(\\\"Train\\\", y_train), (\\\"Val\\\", y_val), (\\\"Test\\\", y_test)]:\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"{name} approval rate: {ys.mean():.3f}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 16. Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Decisions:**\\n\", \"- **Missing numerics** (`LoanAmount`, `Loan_Amount_Term`, `Credit_History`): Impute with median.\\n\", \"- **Missing categoricals** (`Gender`, `Married`, `Dependents`, `Self_Employed`): Impute with mode.\\n\", \"- **Numeric features:** StandardScaler for linear models; trees don't need it but it doesn't hurt.\\n\", \"- **Categorical features:** OneHotEncoder for low-cardinality categories.\\n\", \"- **No leakage:** Everything fit only on training data.\\n\", \"- **Dependents:** Treat `3+` as 3 (numeric).\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Fix Dependents\\n\", \"for ds in [X_train, X_val, X_test]:\\n\", \"    ds[\\\"Dependents\\\"] = ds[\\\"Dependents\\\"].replace(\\\"3+\\\", 3).astype(float)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"num_cols = [\\\"ApplicantIncome\\\", \\\"CoapplicantIncome\\\", \\\"LoanAmount\\\", \\\"Loan_Amount_Term\\\", \\\"Credit_History\\\", \\\"Dependents\\\"]\\n\", \"cat_cols = [\\\"Gender\\\", \\\"Married\\\", \\\"Education\\\", \\\"Self_Employed\\\", \\\"Property_Area\\\"]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"num_pipeline = Pipeline([\\n\", \"    (\\\"impute\\\", SimpleImputer(strategy=\\\"median\\\")),\\n\", \"    (\\\"scale\\\", StandardScaler()),\\n\", \"])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"cat_pipeline = Pipeline([\\n\", \"    (\\\"impute\\\", SimpleImputer(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\")),\\n\", \"    (\\\"onehot\\\", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown=\\\"ignore\\\", sparse_output=False)),\\n\", \"])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer([\\n\", \"    (\\\"num\\\", num_pipeline, num_cols),\\n\", \"    (\\\"cat\\\", cat_pipeline, cat_cols),\\n\", \"])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Numeric: {num_cols}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Categorical: {cat_cols}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 17. Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We create simple derived features that capture borrowing capacity.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"def engineer_features(df_in):\\n\", \"    df_out = df_in.copy()\\n\", \"    df_out[\\\"TotalIncome\\\"] = df_out[\\\"ApplicantIncome\\\"] + df_out[\\\"CoapplicantIncome\\\"]\\n\", \"    df_out[\\\"LoanIncomeRatio\\\"] = df_out[\\\"LoanAmount\\\"].fillna(0) / df_out[\\\"TotalIncome\\\"].clip(lower=1)\\n\", \"    df_out[\\\"LogApplicantIncome\\\"] = np.log1p(df_out[\\\"ApplicantIncome\\\"])\\n\", \"    df_out[\\\"LogLoanAmount\\\"] = np.log1p(df_out[\\\"LoanAmount\\\"].fillna(0))\\n\", \"    return df_out\\n\", \"\\n\", \"X_train = engineer_features(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val = engineer_features(X_val)\\n\", \"X_test = engineer_features(X_test)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Update column lists\\n\", \"new_num = [\\\"TotalIncome\\\", \\\"LoanIncomeRatio\\\", \\\"LogApplicantIncome\\\", \\\"LogLoanAmount\\\"]\\n\", \"num_cols_all = num_cols + new_num\\n\", \"\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer([\\n\", \"    (\\\"num\\\", num_pipeline, num_cols_all),\\n\", \"    (\\\"cat\\\", cat_pipeline, cat_cols),\\n\", \"])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Total features: {len(num_cols_all) + len(cat_cols)} (before encoding)\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 18. Baseline Model\\n\", \"\\n\", \"DummyClassifier sets the floor. We then try LogReg and Random Forest.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"results = {}\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dummy = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", DummyClassifier(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\", random_state=SEED))])\\n\", \"dummy.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"results[\\\"Dummy\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, dummy.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, dummy.predict(X_val))}\\n\", \"print(\\\"Dummy:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"Dummy\\\"].items()})\\n\", \"\\n\", \"lr = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED))])\\n\", \"lr.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"y_prob_lr = lr.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"LogReg\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_lr)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"LogReg:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"LogReg\\\"].items()})\\n\", \"\\n\", \"rf = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED, n_jobs=-1))])\\n\", \"rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"y_prob_rf = rf.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"RF\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_rf)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"RF:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"RF\\\"].items()})\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 19. LazyPredict Benchmark\\n\", \"\\n\", \"LazyPredict fits ~30 classifiers quickly. With only ~614 rows, some models may overfit — treat results as directional.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_lp = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val_lp = preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"lazy = LazyClassifier(verbose=0, ignore_warnings=True, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"models_lp, _ = lazy.fit(X_train_lp, X_val_lp, y_train, y_val)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Top 15 models:\\\")\\n\", \"models_lp.head(15)\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 20. FLAML AutoML Run\\n\", \"\\n\", \"FLAML optimises for accuracy (balanced classes are close enough). Short budget due to small dataset.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"automl = AutoML()\\n\", \"X_train_fl = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val_fl = preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"automl.fit(\\n\", \"    X_train_fl, y_train,\\n\", \"    task=\\\"classification\\\",\\n\", \"    metric=\\\"accuracy\\\",\\n\", \"    time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,\\n\", \"    seed=SEED,\\n\", \"    verbose=0,\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best model: {automl.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\", \"y_pred_fl = automl.predict(X_val_fl)\\n\", \"y_prob_fl = automl.predict_proba(X_val_fl)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"FLAML\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred_fl), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, y_pred_fl), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_fl)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"FLAML:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"FLAML\\\"].items()})\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 21. Top 3 Model Selection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Based on LazyPredict and FLAML results, we select:\\n\", \"1. **LightGBM / ExtraTrees** — often top on tabular data\\n\", \"2. **XGBoost / AdaBoost** — gradient boosting alternative\\n\", \"3. **GradientBoosting** — sklearn ensemble\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"try:\\n\", \"    from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier\\n\", \"    has_lgbm = True\\n\", \"except ImportError:\\n\", \"    has_lgbm = False\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    from xgboost import XGBClassifier\\n\", \"    has_xgb = True\\n\", \"except ImportError:\\n\", \"    has_xgb = False\\n\", \"\\n\", \"top3 = {}\\n\", \"if has_lgbm:\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"LightGBM\\\"] = LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=300, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=4, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED, verbose=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"ExtraTrees\\\"] = ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=300, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED, n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"if has_xgb:\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"XGBoost\\\"] = XGBClassifier(n_estimators=300, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=4, scale_pos_weight=(y_train==0).sum()/(y_train==1).sum(), random_state=SEED, verbosity=0)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"AdaBoost\\\"] = AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"top3[\\\"GradientBoosting\\\"] = GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=200, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=3, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top 3: {list(top3.keys())}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 22. Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We train on the full training set and evaluate on the held-out test set.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_t = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_test_t = preprocessor.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"final_results = {}\\n\", \"for name, model in top3.items():\\n\", \"    model.fit(X_train_t, y_train)\\n\", \"    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_t)\\n\", \"    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test_t)[:, 1]\\n\", \"    final_results[name] = {\\n\", \"        \\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"Precision\\\": precision_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob),\\n\", \"        \\\"PR-AUC\\\": average_precision_score(y_test, y_prob),\\n\", \"    }\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{name}:\\\")\\n\", \"    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=[\\\"Rejected\\\", \\\"Approved\\\"]))\\n\", \"\\n\", \"results_df = pd.DataFrame(final_results).T\\n\", \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Final Test Results ===\\\")\\n\", \"results_df\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, len(top3), figsize=(5*len(top3), 4))\\nif len(top3) == 1: axes = [axes]\\nfor ax, (name, model) in zip(axes, top3.items()):\\n    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(y_test, model.predict(X_test_t), ax=ax, cmap=\\\"Blues\\\", display_labels=[\\\"Rejected\\\",\\\"Approved\\\"])\\n    ax.set_title(name)\\nplt.suptitle(\\\"Confusion Matrices — Test Set\\\", y=1.02)\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\nfor name, model in top3.items():\\n    RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(model, X_test_t, y_test, ax=axes[0], name=name)\\n    PrecisionRecallDisplay.from_estimator(model, X_test_t, y_test, ax=axes[1], name=name)\\naxes[0].plot([0,1],[0,1],\\\"k--\\\",alpha=0.5)\\naxes[0].set_title(\\\"ROC Curves\\\")\\naxes[1].set_title(\\\"PR Curves\\\")\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 23. Error Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We examine misclassifications to understand failure modes.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"best_name = list(top3.keys())[0]\\nbest_model = top3[best_name]\\ny_pred_best = best_model.predict(X_test_t)\\n\\nfn_mask = (y_test == 1) & (y_pred_best == 0)\\nfp_mask = (y_test == 0) & (y_pred_best == 1)\\nprint(f\\\"False Negatives (rejected good applicants): {fn_mask.sum()}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"False Positives (approved bad applicants): {fp_mask.sum()}\\\")\\n\\ntest_df = X_test.copy()\\ntest_df[\\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"correct\\\"\\ntest_df.loc[fn_mask.values, \\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"false_negative\\\"\\ntest_df.loc[fp_mask.values, \\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"false_positive\\\"\\n\\nfor col in [\\\"Credit_History\\\", \\\"TotalIncome\\\", \\\"LoanAmount\\\"]:\\n    if col in test_df.columns:\\n        print(f\\\"\\\\n{col} — mean by error type:\\\")\\n        print(test_df.groupby(\\\"error_type\\\")[col].mean())\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 24. Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Key findings:**\\n\", \"1. **Credit_History** is by far the strongest predictor — applicants with good credit history (1) are much more likely to be approved.\\n\", \"2. **Total income** matters — higher combined applicant + coapplicant income improves approval odds.\\n\", \"3. **Property area** — Semi-urban areas show higher approval rates, possibly reflecting different property values or risk profiles.\\n\", \"4. **Loan-to-income ratio** — lower ratios correlate with approval.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Business recommendations:**\\n\", \"- Credit history should be the primary screening variable\\n\", \"- Coapplicant income significantly improves borrowing capacity\\n\", \"- Consider risk-adjusted interest rates based on loan-to-income ratio\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 25. Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Small dataset:** Only ~614 rows — models may not generalise well.\\n\", \"2. **Missing data:** Several columns have missing values, imputation adds noise.\\n\", \"3. **Fairness:** Gender and Married status as features raise fairness concerns in real lending.\\n\", \"4. **Simplified target:** Real loan approval involves many more factors (employment verification, property valuation, etc.).\\n\", \"5. **No temporal information:** No application date or economic context.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 26. How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Cross-validation:** With only 614 rows, use 5-fold stratified CV instead of single split.\\n\", \"2. **Remove sensitive attributes:** Drop Gender and Married for fairness-aware modelling.\\n\", \"3. **Feature interactions:** Credit_History × Income, Education × Self_Employed.\\n\", \"4. **Ensemble methods:** Stack models for more robust predictions.\\n\", \"5. **Larger dataset:** Seek production-scale lending data for realistic benchmarks.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 27. Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- **Regulatory compliance:** Lending models must comply with fair lending laws (no discrimination by gender, race, etc.).\\n\", \"- **Explainability:** Every rejection must be explainable — use SHAP or LIME.\\n\", \"- **Monitoring:** Track approval rate drift and model performance monthly.\\n\", \"- **Human-in-the-loop:** Models should recommend, not decide — loan officers make final calls.\\n\", \"- **Data freshness:** Retrain with updated credit bureau data regularly.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 28. Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Including Loan_ID** as a feature (it's just an identifier).\\n\", \"2. **Not encoding Dependents** `3+` as a numeric value.\\n\", \"3. **Fitting imputers on full data** before train/test split.\\n\", \"4. **Ignoring Credit_History** — it dominates prediction and may indicate data leakage if it encodes the outcome.\\n\", \"5. **Overinterpreting results** from a 614-row dataset.\\n\", \"6. **Not addressing fairness** — using Gender directly in a lending model.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 29. Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Fairness audit:** Remove Gender and Married. Does model performance change significantly?\\n\", \"2. **Cross-validation:** Replace single split with 5-fold stratified CV. Report mean ± std.\\n\", \"3. **Feature importance:** Which features does LightGBM rank highest? Does this match your intuition?\\n\", \"4. **Threshold analysis:** What threshold maximises F1? What about maximising recall?\\n\", \"5. **Missing data:** Try different imputation strategies (KNN imputer, iterative imputer). Does it help?\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 30. Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Aspect | Detail |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Task** | Binary classification — loan approval prediction |\\n\", \"| **Dataset** | ~614 rows, 11 features, ~69% approval rate |\\n\", \"| **Best metric focus** | Accuracy and F1 |\\n\", \"| **Baseline** | DummyClassifier ~69% accuracy |\\n\", \"| **Key insight** | Credit_History dominates — nearly a single-feature classifier |\\n\", \"| **Limitation** | Very small dataset — results are illustrative, not production-grade |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**What you learned:**\\n\", \"- How to handle mixed data types with ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"- Proper imputation strategies for numerics vs categoricals\\n\", \"- Why small datasets require careful cross-validation\\n\", \"- Fairness considerations in automated lending decisions\\n\", \"- The full benchmark → AutoML → top 3 evaluation pipeline\"]\n",
